name: "Skelly Guy" by Richard F. Yates (Holy Fool)
description: [Ink on paper with digital embellishments and color.] Just cause he's dead doesn't mean he has to look bad, right? This fellow wasn't that interested in fashion when he was alive, but now that he has an eternity to show up in weird ghost photos, he's decided to take a little pride in his appearance! ---Richard F. Yates (Holy Fool)
